# Headless CMS monorepo

## Layout

| Directory | Stack | Cursor rules |
|-----------|-------|----------------|
| `next-headless-cms-fe/` | Next.js multi-tenant CMS | **`.cursor/rules/`** — use these for all frontend work |
| `headless-cms-backend/` | Strapi v5 | No dedicated rules yet — follow Strapi conventions in that folder |

## Where to look

- **Human docs**: repo root `README.md`; frontend `next-headless-cms-fe/docs/` (`DEVELOPMENT.md`, `BUILD-VERIFICATION.md`)
- **Frontend architecture, blocks, deploy, i18n**: `next-headless-cms-fe/.cursor/rules/`
- **Start (agents)**: `next-headless-cms-fe/.cursor/rules/rules-sync.mdc`
- **Per tenant**: `next-headless-cms-fe/.cursor/rules/tenants/{tenant-id}/catalog.mdc`

## GitHub Actions

Workflows are at repo root: `.github/workflows/`. They set `working-directory: next-headless-cms-fe` for frontend jobs.

## When editing backend

Strapi schemas and seed data live in `headless-cms-backend/`. Frontend `dataAdapter: "strapi"` and `StrapiAdapter` are not fully wired yet — coordinate API shape with `next-headless-cms-fe/src/core/types/` when you connect them.

Do not duplicate frontend tenant catalogs for backend-only changes unless the public API contract for pages/blocks changes.
